  "body": "## Description\r\n  \r\nNo validator graffiti flag. Many users that join the Medalla testnet will want to receive a POAP badge for running a validator.  \r\n  \r\nThere is a `--graffiti` flag for the lighthouse beacon client which appears to work, however, the instructions at the [POAP page](https://medalla.beaconcha.in/poap) only refers to the validator which will cause confusion for people using lighthouse.\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nLighthouse 0.1.2-9ae9df80\r\n\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nNo graffiti flag for validator.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nGraffiti flag option available for validator.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nEither:\r\n1. Add a graffiti flag to the validator, or\r\n2. Update the Lighthouse Book with instructions on how to add a beacon client graffiti flag to receive a POAP badge and reach out to medalla.beaconcha.in to update the instructions on the POAP page for lighthouse.\r\n",
